# Vie Locale Destructive Actions

## Destruction & archival — confirmation modals encouraged
Use a **focused confirmation dialog** before irreversible loss or materially significant state (`delete`, permanent removal, GDPR erasure helpers, destructive imports).

Requirements:
- **Title states the consequence** plainly (e.g. “Supprimer cette annonce ?”).
- **Body summarizes what disappears** — counts, commune scope — without fear-mongering copy.
- **Primary button names the irrevocable verb** (“Supprimer définitivement”, “Archiver”) paired with **secondary “Annuler”** at equal prominence (no shrunken dismiss).
- When available, mention **recovery window / soft-delete** rules honestly.

Avoid guilt scripting (“vous allez sérieusement perdre…”); factual is enough.

## Exits vs sludge (`ethical-nudge-ux`)
**Forbidden friction patterns** when users leave flows: unsubscribe, downgrade, cancel onboarding, logout, commune switch-away, discard draft with explicit intent.

Examples of **disallowed sludge:**
- burying abandon/cancel beneath extra screens versus entry
- timer pressure to stay
- deceptive “sticky” dismissal targets
- extra arbitrary CAPTCHAs only on exit paths

Leaving or canceling stays **≤ effort** comparable to initiating the flow.
